      - date: 2024-09-09T15:34:13.831Z
        author: PositionHunter
        text: >-
          @Karthikshastri ok, so this always works for me when consolidating, it
          seems simple - but I didn't think of it until someone told me. 


          So list out every stock you have in a spreadsheet. Now number them
          from 1 to however many stocks you have but crucially, number 1 is the
          stock you think is your best idea and that you have the most
          conviction in and go through the list until you've identified what are
          your best and worst ideas. Following that - cull everything below the
          number of stocks you want to hold.


          It's ruthless, but it works.
        responses: 0
      - date: 2024-09-09T15:28:53.861Z
