    author: TheDividendExperiment
    text: >-
      Rite-Aid. Speculated that of the two buyout outcomes it was a binary
      yes/no and both would end up being beneficial for me based on the price I
      bought in at.


      A - it would be approved, and Walgreens would pay me $6 for my shares


      B - It was not approved, and the shares would still likely be above my
      buying price and being free from the bureaucracy of waiting for an
      acquisition would help the share price.


      Turns out that there was a secret 3rd option where Walgreens ended up
      buying a smaller number of stores that they didn;t need approval for. Of
      course, these were also the best locations of stores.


      Shares plummeted (as they should, it was a terrible deal for $RAD
      holders). Always sticks out in my mind as an example in my mind of really
      poor shareholder stewardship by management
